==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thoracoplasty
<hw>Tho`ra*co*plas"ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Thorax</ets> + <ets>plasty</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A remodeling or reshaping of the thorax; especially, the operation
of removing the ribs, so as to obliterate the pleural cavity in cases of
empyema.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thoracostraca</ent>⟦br⟧
